main event: A round, white object the size of a dime was observed in the sky near Oliver Springs, Tennessee on July 15, 1958.
interesting points: The object appeared to fade gradually and was brighter than an evening star.
The object traveled in a straight path from northwest to southeast.
The sighting lasted between 1 to 1.5 minutes.
The object was similar to another UFO reported by the 6328th in the same area on the same date.
The report mentions a possible explanation that the object could have been the moon.
